T1  - The equity premium and the concentration of aggregate shocks
AU  - Mankiw, N.Gregory
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 17
IS  - 1
SP  - 211
EP  - 219
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/09/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(86)90012-7
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X86900127
AB  - This paper examines an economy in which aggregate shocks are not dispersed equally throughout the population. Instead, while these shocks affect all individuals ex ante, they are concentrated among a few ex post. The equity premium in general depends on the concentration of these aggregate shocks; it follows that one cannot estimate the degree of risk aversion from aggregate data alone. These findings suggest that the empirical usefulness of aggregation theorems for capital asset pricing models is limited.
ER  - 

